en_6821902_0	A group of political party activists who were engaging canvasing ahead of the general election met with an accident earlier today.
en_6821902_1	One youth, 22 years of age, died and four others suffered injuries as a result of the motor accident.
en_6821902_2	According to the police, the victims were supporters of Minister Duminda Dissanayake.
en_6821902_3	The remains of the deceased are currently lying at the Rambewa Hospital while the injured have been admitted to the Anuradhapura General Hospital and two were moved to the Intensive Care Unit for further treatment.
en_6821902_4	According to the Police Media Spokesperson ASP Ruwan Gunasekera, the van in question was driven by the OIC of the Anti Vice Squad of Anuradhapura, who is now in police custody.
